    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Fuel System - Removal - Fuel Filter
        Header Assembly and Intake Manifold
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="6">
        <title>Fuel Filter Header Assembly and Intake Manifold</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">
                <hotlnk document="eges2651_234.xml" xrefid="f2651203" appearance="hottext">Drain fuel filter
                    assembly</hotlnk>, if not done so already.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Drain fuel bowl by performing the following steps:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Have a suitable container handy to catch draining fuel. Open drain valve completely. In
                    most cases, the portion of fuel
                    <emph type="bold">below</emph>
                    the fuel strainer will pour out.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Turn primer pump assembly knob counter-clockwise to unlock. Pump primer knob
                    approximately 3-4 times to force fuel through strainer.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Turn primer pump assembly knob clockwise to lock.</para>
                <figure id="f2651206.1" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figh11/H11025.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                    <caption>Removing fuel bowl and strainer</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Use a 24 mm or 15/16 inch open end wrench to unthread the bowl from the housing.</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651206.5" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh11/H11026.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Strainer and heater assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel strainer</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Heater assembly (optional equipment)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel bowl O-ring</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove both the fuel bowl and strainer for cleaning replacement. Discard fuel bowl O-ring.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651207" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh11/H11019.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Fuel filter assembly mounting bolts</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Bolts, M8 x 100</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove three mounting bolts (M8 x 100) and fuel filter assembly from intake manifold.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651208" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh11/H11043.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Removing the fuel filter outlet gasket</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Discard the fuel filter outlet gasket between fuel filter assembly and intake manifold.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651208.2" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh11/H11055.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Removing the fuel rail plug assembly (2)</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the plug assembly (M12) from each end of the intake manifold and discard O-ring seal.
                You may also need to remove the rear engine lifting eye to gain access to remove the rear plug.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651208.4" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh11/H11056.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Removing the fuel valve assembly (air bleed and pressure test port)</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the fuel valve assembly (air bleed and pressure test port), located at the front end
                of the intake manifold. Discard O-ring seal.
            </para>
        </step1>
